	(167,2,'2013-10-23 23:02:41','2013-10-23 23:02:41','Matthew facilitates the successful execution of Projects as AGD\'s COO and DirectProject Manager. His areas of expertise are: Product Management, Product Marketing, Project Management, Operations Management, Strategic Planning &amp; Execution, Operational Excellence, Change Management, Product/Process Transfer, Human Capital Management, Training &amp; Development.\n\nHe takes on a variety of Project Management Consulting roles with our clients (both startup and well established companies), focusing on new product development and technologies for desktop/web/mobile/cloud based applications.\n\nThe Technical Stuff:\nApplication Project Management, Agile/Scrum Methodology, Stage-Gate, Waterfall, MS Office, Microsoft Project, Adobe CS6,Crystal Reports, Salesforce, UX Technical Documentation... and a bunch of SaaS Applications.','Matthew Santos','','inherit','open','open','','134-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-23 23:02:41','2013-10-23 23:02:41','',134,'http://www.agdesigngroup.com/dev/?p=167',0,'revision','',0),
	(168,2,'2013-10-31 22:28:03','2013-10-31 22:28:03','Arlene Santos brings over a decade of creative design and strategic marketing experience. She provides key strategic vision and leadership across cross-disciplinary development and oversees the successful execution of all creative strategies. Arlene has the unique ability to interpret her clients\' communications strategies and develop creative approaches and treatments that align with that strategy. Arlene routinely leads projects and campaigns in cross matrix reporting environments, often advising VP and CXO level management in the areas of innovation, user-engagement, brand recognition and optimization. Arlene has lead teams that have designed and executed hundreds of UI/UX design/development projects, collecting award-winning results along the way.\n\nArlene received two Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) degrees in Graphic Design from the University of San Francisco (USF) and California College of the Arts (CCA), graduating Magna-Cum-Laude. Arlene began freelance consulting, building her clientele since 2001 and has grown AGD into a prominent UI/UX consultancy sought-out by clients such as Hitachi, Western Digital, Johnson &amp; Johnson.\n\nArlene is well received by her clients and bases her success on the success of each client and the results they achieve. She has created long lasting relationships with clients that lead to ongoing projects and campaigns. She contributes her success to her design process, strong work ethic, and dedication to projects.\n\nArlene actively participates in her community and sits on the board of directors for Mt. Diablo Business Women and serves as the co-chair for Women In Consulting, East Bay.','Arlene Santos','','inherit','open','open','','55-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-31 22:28:03','2013-10-31 22:28:03','',55,'http://www.agdesigngroup.com/dev/?p=168',0,'revision','',0),
	(169,2,'2013-10-20 06:35:58','2013-10-20 06:35:58','Damon is our Senior UI/UX Designer and Developer/Prototyper. He posses the rare skill sets of Designer and Developer. He has a thorough understanding of the full software development life cycle with strong hands-on development experience, a passion for innovative user experience and can create commercial quality web products.\n\nHe has 10+ years of front-end development experience, rapid prototyping, and creating responsive web designs that work well on all devices, especially mobile and tablet.\n\nThe Technical Stuff:\nAdobe CS6, Javascript/jQuery, CSS 3, XHTML, HTML5, AJAX, XML, JSON, DOM, PHP, Wordpress, Drupal','Damon Hastings','','inherit','open','open','','53-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-20 06:35:58','2013-10-20 06:35:58','',53,'http://www.agdesigngroup.com/dev/?p=169',0,'revision','',0),
	(170,2,'2013-10-20 06:52:36','2013-10-20 06:52:36','Perlita adds a flare to the AG Design team. Poised, articulate and with a penchant for dry humor, Perlita keeps the joy de vivre at AGD.\n\nPerlita is responsible for overseeing project direction. She adeptly manages client expectations and direction, and the design teams vision. Perlita is often responsible for coordinating project production. Her writing savvy has aided many clients with developing copy, press releases, and editing.\n\nWhen she is not fiddling with words, Perlita enjoys cooking, wine tasting, camping, going to sporting events and spending time with her family.\n\nThe Technical Stuff:\nMS Office, Microsoft Project, Adobe CS6, Social Media, PR, Content Management Systems (Drupal, Joomla, Wordpress, Apostrophe, Concrete5), CMS Trainings &amp; User Documentation Manuals.','Perlita Herrera','','inherit','open','open','','135-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-20 06:52:36','2013-10-20 06:52:36','',135,'http://www.agdesigngroup.com/dev/?p=170',0,'revision','',0),
	(171,2,'2013-10-20 07:11:12','2013-10-20 07:11:12','Jennifer wins the office trophy of Most Outgoing. Her laugh is infectious. With little direction, Jennifer, or Jenn, as she likes to be called, is able to develop a simple concept into a visual masterpiece.\n\nJennifers love for design was fostered at an early age. Her talent has been crafted by years of experience. While her love affair began with print design, Jennifers skills spans the spectrum of media.\n\nWhen Jennifer isnt pairing beautiful typography with vivid imagery, Jennifer explores the Bay Area in search of good eats, antique and thrift store treasures, and scenic running trails.\n\nThe Technical Stuff:\nAdobe CS6, MS Office, iOS/Android Mobile App Design, UI Specification &amp; UX Flow Documentation mounting mocks and on black boards the old school way.','Jennifer Vaughn','','inherit','open','open','','136-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-20 07:11:12','2013-10-20 07:11:12','',136,'http://www.agdesigngroup.com/dev/?p=171',0,'revision','',0),
	(172,2,'2013-10-20 07:19:21','2013-10-20 07:19:21','Olivia is the newest member of our team. Her previous graphic design work entailed creating various print items and digital elements, assisting in projects (design, layout production, photography), and photography research, while assisting with a variety of graphic design projects including products such as flyers, brochures, posters, banners, web graphics, icons/logos, templates, and style guides.\n\nThe Technical Stuff:\nAdobe CS6, MS Office, Responsive/Mobile/Tablet Design','Olivia Lopez','','inherit','open','open','','137-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-20 07:19:21','2013-10-20 07:19:21','',137,'http://www.agdesigngroup.com/dev/?p=172',0,'revision','',0),
